; Expected-diagnostic case (R3c-i): mutually-exclusive algebra pragmas on a
; functor. `@invertible` (the fold/unfold class) and `@recompute` (the opaque
; fallback) cannot both apply; the parser rejects the second with a clean
; "Conflicting ... a functor cannot be both invertible and recompute"
; diagnostic plus a note at the first, in all 4 optimization modes (the reject
; is in the parser, before any optimization runs). See DeltaRelationalIR.md
; §7.1 and runall.sh's all-modes-diagnostic list.
#functor cnt(aggregate i32 V, summary i32 C) @invertible @recompute.
#message m(i32 X).
#local t(i32 X).
#query out_t(free i32 N).
t(X) : m(X).
out_t(N) : cnt(X, N) over (i32 X) { t(X) }.
